You will be given an array a and a value x. All you need to do is check whether the provided array contains the value.

Array can contain numbers or strings. X can be either.

Return true if the array contains the value, false if not.





function check(a, x) {
 for (let i = 0; i < a.length; i++){
   if (a[i] === x) {
     return true; 
     } else {
  }
}
  return false; 
}

//input 1 is array 
//input 2 is a value 
//check if array contains the value 
//return true if the array === value else return false 

Things I learned: 

- If you put the return false inside the for loop the function will only check the first value if it meets the condition and will not continue through the loop. 
